According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Kombucha Market was valued at USD 1.91 billion in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 2.32 billion in 2025 to USD 7.16 billion by 2032, registering an impressive CAGR of 21.3% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing rapid expansion as consumers increasingly embrace functional beverages that promote digestive health, immunity, and overall wellness. Growing awareness of probiotic-rich foods, rising demand for clean-label products, and continuous product innovation featuring adaptogens, botanical extracts, and low-sugar formulations are transforming kombucha from a niche fermented drink into a mainstream beverage category across global markets.
